  "prompt": "What universities does Lakeland Financial recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Lakeland Financial Services offers a variety of career opportunities for new graduates, and their recruitment strategies typically focus on sourcing talented individuals from a range of educational backgrounds and institutions. While specific universities and preferred majors can vary based on the roles available and the company\u2019s current needs, here is some general information that may help:\n\n### **Universities Commonly Recruited From**\n\nLakeland Financial has a presence in multiple regions across Canada, and as such, they often recruit from universities that are prominent in those areas. Some of the universities that companies in the financial sector, including Lakeland Financial, commonly recruit from include:\n\n- **University of Waterloo**\n- **University of Toronto**\n- **Western University**\n- **Queen\u2019s University**\n- **McMaster University**\n- **Simon Fraser University**\n- **Dalhousie University**\n- **University of British Columbia**\n- **York University**\n\n*Note:* This list is not exhaustive, and Lakeland Financial may recruit from a broader range of institutions based on their hiring needs.\n\n### **Preferred Majors and Educational Backgrounds**\n\nLakeland Financial typically seeks candidates with academic backgrounds that align with the roles they are hiring for. Common majors and areas of study include:\n\n- **Finance:** Understanding of financial principles, investment strategies, and market analysis.\n- **Business Administration:** Knowledge of business operations, management, and organizational behavior.\n- **Economics:** Insights into economic theory, data analysis, and economic policy.\n- **Accounting:** Expertise in financial reporting, auditing, and tax preparation.\n- **Computer Science/Information Technology:** Especially for roles in IT, data analysis, and cybersecurity.\n- **Marketing:** For positions related to market research, communications, and brand management.\n- **Mathematics/Statistics:** Valuable for roles involving data analysis, risk assessment, and quantitative modeling.\n- **Human Resources:** For positions focused on talent acquisition, employee relations, and organizational development.\n\n### **Additional Skills and Qualifications**\n\nBeyond majors, Lakeland Financial often looks for the following in new graduates:\n\n- **Relevant Internships or Co-op Experience:** Practical experience in financial services or related fields.\n- **Technical Skills:** Proficiency in software relevant to the position, such as Microsoft Excel, financial modeling tools, CRM systems, or programming languages for technical roles.\n- **Soft Skills:** Strong communication, teamwork, problem-solving abilities, and adaptability.\n- **Certifications:** While not always required, certifications like CFA, CPA, or others relevant to specific roles can be advantageous.\n\n### **How to Stay Updated**\n\nRecruitment strategies and preferred backgrounds can evolve, so it\u2019s a good idea to:\n\n1. **Visit Lakeland Financial\u2019s Official Careers Page:** This will provide the most up-to-date information on available positions, requirements, and recruitment events.\n   \n2. **Attend Career Fairs and Recruitment Events:** Lakeland Financial may participate in university career fairs, webinars, and other events where you can learn more and connect with recruiters.\n\n3. **Follow on Professional Networks:** Platforms like LinkedIn can offer insights into the company\u2019s latest job postings and hiring trends.\n\n4. **Connect with Alumni:** Reach out to alumni from your university who work or have worked at Lakeland Financial to gain firsthand insights.\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\nWhile specific recruitment targets can vary, Lakeland Financial generally seeks well-rounded candidates from reputable universities with strong academic backgrounds relevant to the roles they are offering. Focusing on building relevant skills, gaining practical experience, and staying informed through official channels will enhance your prospects of being recruited as a new graduate.\n\nFor the most accurate and detailed information, I recommend visiting [Lakeland Financial\u2019s Careers Page](https://www.lakelandfinancial.ca/en/careers.aspx) or contacting their HR department directly.",
  "response_tokens": [
